enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve extracting text from elements, making them suitable for similar test setups.
The hasText() method checks if an element has text, which can be used to set up elements with and without text for testing eachText().
The traverse method can be used to modify the state of elements before calling eachText(), ensuring that the elements are in the correct state for text extraction.
The filter method can be used to filter elements before calling eachText(), ensuring that only the relevant elements are processed.
